Tandem walking is a straightforward yet effective exercise for enhancing balance and coordination. By walking with one foot placed directly in front of the other, this exercise challenges your balance and engages your core and lower leg muscles. Tandem walking is particularly useful for improving stability and can help reduce the risk of falls. It is a practical exercise that can be performed anywhere, making it an accessible option for those looking to improve their balance and coordination. Regular practice of tandem walking can lead to better walking mechanics and increased confidence in daily movements.

• Stand with your feet together.
• Step forward with your right foot, placing your heel directly in front of your left toes.
• Then step forward with your left foot, placing your heel directly in front of your right toes.
• Continue walking in a straight line for several steps.
• Turn around and repeat the exercise walking back in the opposite direction.
